				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />

<br />
You are barking right up my tree.  I duo a 65 bardess and a 57 cleric.  I use the two to aa each other and level my cleric.  It is also handy for the elusive leadership AA's.  I run two computers though.  Many a horror story of two boxing and not getting the cleric out in time.  On two separate machine it is fairly easy to twist and heal...  Even mark the npcs with a little keystroke mapping.  h*ll I might even get a macro pad.  d*mn posting this gave me even more ideas.  
<br />

<br />
Kiting a bard with a cleric in tow is fun.  Challenging for the one stroke cleric and the 1,000 stroke bardess.  BARDS ARE BEST!  Funny thing is, Bard duoing is really fairly easy combo with most classes on two puters.  I just like having tons of Dot hate and being able to heal up and bring on more mobs.
<br />

<br />
Right now I reap havoc in everything up to POV!  Enjoy the duo man whatever you choose!
<br />

<br />
~Love</span></td>
