				<td colspan="2"><span>I two-box a 65 bard/65 cleric combo.  You kind of play the cleric in between song taps. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />   I can go so many places by myself with lull/pacify, invis, IVU, selo's, etc.  I just never know if I'm a fast cleric or a bard that heals.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I was going to recommend bard/cleric without reservation until I saw this line in your post:
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I would also like my duo to be able to take on some big named mobs...</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
When I want to take tough mobs down, I use the cleric to root, and I stack chants with my bard.  Against highly MR mobs or heavy hitters, root breaking/resistance gets to be an issue.  A BST would let you do more toe-to-toe fighting if that's your thing.  Just know that the bard/cleric is more finesse, bst/cleric is more straightforward.
<br />

<br />
Also, many posts I've read say cleric/bst is a great combo for high level duoing.  Funny, having said all that, I'd never give up my bard. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Good luck on your choice!
<br />

<br />
Aryya</span></td>
